3
00:01:28,210 --> 00:01:30,720
[Episode 34]

4
00:01:53,430 --> 00:01:54,600
In 1984,

5
00:01:56,500 --> 00:01:59,130
many of you were not born.

6
00:01:59,800 --> 00:02:02,280
That year, I started my flight career

7
00:02:03,400 --> 00:02:05,210
with Fanhai Airlines.

8
00:02:05,800 --> 00:02:07,890
Some young colleagues may not know

9
00:02:09,509 --> 00:02:11,510
what I went through

10
00:02:12,420 --> 00:02:13,600
in 2004.

11
00:02:15,140 --> 00:02:15,860
That year,

12
00:02:16,550 --> 00:02:18,970
the plane was at 101 altitude.

13
00:02:19,810 --> 00:02:21,610
The plane was suddenly damaged.

14
00:02:22,010 --> 00:02:23,270
I was the captain then.

15
00:02:23,590 --> 00:02:25,390
Mr. Jiang was the first officer.

16
00:02:25,470 --> 00:02:26,760
We cooperate and

17
00:02:27,430 --> 00:02:30,310
successfully landed in a field outside the runway,

18
00:02:31,010 --> 00:02:33,220
and protected all tourists.

19
00:02:35,230 --> 00:02:36,230
This event

20
00:02:36,530 --> 00:02:38,000
has changed my life.

21
00:02:38,450 --> 00:02:40,380
I think it also changed everyone

22
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:41,730
that was on this flight.

23
00:02:43,570 --> 00:02:44,200
Later on,

24
00:02:45,540 --> 00:02:47,850
we became known as the Hero Team.

25
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:49,600
But

26
00:02:51,610 --> 00:02:53,550
I hope that there will be no more heroes

27
00:02:53,550 --> 00:02:54,600
in our industry.

28
00:02:55,370 --> 00:02:56,930
Because this can prove that

29
00:02:57,020 --> 00:02:59,760
our every flight is extremely safe.

30
00:03:01,770 --> 00:03:02,640
For me,

31
00:03:03,100 --> 00:03:05,500
protecting every flight

32
00:03:05,690 --> 00:03:08,150
is the priority and my only responsibility.

33
00:03:08,570 --> 00:03:09,850
Nothing can

34
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:11,960
can surpass their lives.

35
00:03:22,750 --> 00:03:23,680
Unfortunately,

36
00:03:24,460 --> 00:03:26,020
because of my health,

37
00:03:26,980 --> 00:03:29,350
I have to say goodbye to the sky in advance.

38
00:03:30,070 --> 00:03:32,320
The 27,000-hour flight hours I have

39
00:03:32,970 --> 00:03:34,460
will stop today.

40
00:03:35,380 --> 00:03:37,440
In addition to administrative work,

41
00:03:37,480 --> 00:03:40,650
I will continue to be the instructor of the simulator.

42
00:03:41,390 --> 00:03:41,960
Lastly,

43
00:03:42,970 --> 00:03:44,180
I want to hold a simple

44
00:03:44,630 --> 00:03:46,030
succession ceremony.

45
00:03:46,650 --> 00:03:47,700
May I have

46
00:03:47,920 --> 00:03:50,280
the flight crew that was on the same flight as me today

47
00:03:50,280 --> 00:03:51,280
come on the stage.

48
00:04:03,390 --> 00:04:04,570
The number is not right.

49
00:04:04,570 --> 00:04:06,300
Why are we all male pilots here?

50
00:04:06,730 --> 00:04:08,380
I remember there was a female pilot

51
00:04:08,380 --> 00:04:09,770
on the plane today too.

52
00:04:11,140 --> 00:04:11,800
Cheng Xiao,

53
00:04:13,480 --> 00:04:14,340
please come up.

54
00:04:41,880 --> 00:04:43,250
I want to ask you.

55
00:04:44,440 --> 00:04:46,070
Every time in the cockpit,

56
00:04:46,990 --> 00:04:48,780
when you se the passenger

57
00:04:49,190 --> 00:04:52,180
from the corridor bridge,

58
00:04:52,470 --> 00:04:54,060
what do you observe

59
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:55,820
and what do you notice?

60
00:04:59,380 --> 00:05:00,490
I will observe

61
00:05:00,900 --> 00:05:03,260
whether the operators on the corridor bridge are in place

62
00:05:03,260 --> 00:05:04,930
and if the tow truck is in place.

63
00:05:04,930 --> 00:05:06,130
If there is any delay,

64
00:05:06,130 --> 00:05:07,800
it will affect my operation.

65
00:05:10,820 --> 00:05:11,740
I will observe

66
00:05:11,770 --> 00:05:13,970
if there are any suspicious passengers

67
00:05:14,380 --> 00:05:16,540
or if there are any mentally unstable

68
00:05:16,570 --> 00:05:17,610
or drunk passengers,

69
00:05:17,610 --> 00:05:19,670
or passengers who'd toss a lucky coin

70
00:05:19,780 --> 00:05:21,130
into the engine.

71
00:05:23,280 --> 00:05:24,600
If we find it immediately,

72
00:05:24,600 --> 00:05:27,200
we can stop the potential danger immediately.

73
00:05:31,710 --> 00:05:32,510
That's right.

74
00:05:33,300 --> 00:05:34,830
Cheng Xiao, what about you?

75
00:05:43,060 --> 00:05:43,790
I would think

76
00:05:45,550 --> 00:05:46,450
of them

77
00:05:46,530 --> 00:05:48,420
are ordinary people.

78
00:05:51,690 --> 00:05:52,540
I'll see if

79
00:05:52,570 --> 00:05:54,100
they're happy or sad today.

80
00:05:57,770 --> 00:05:59,220
I'll think about

81
00:05:59,650 --> 00:06:01,780
what kind of journey they are going on.

82
00:06:02,370 --> 00:06:03,830
Are they going out to work?

83
00:06:04,420 --> 00:06:07,280
Or are they going home to reunite with their family?

84
00:06:08,660 --> 00:06:09,880
In this journey,

85
00:06:12,960 --> 00:06:15,420
would they need any of our crew members' help

86
00:06:16,800 --> 00:06:17,400
and care?

87
00:06:27,430 --> 00:06:29,490
They are all answers I wanted to hear.

88
00:06:30,910 --> 00:06:31,900
All these years,

89
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:35,650
the most satisfying moment I had

90
00:06:36,970 --> 00:06:38,510
is not a promotion, a raise,

91
00:06:38,970 --> 00:06:40,030
awards, or praise,

92
00:06:40,659 --> 00:06:41,770
but every time

93
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:43,640
I send every passenger

94
00:06:43,670 --> 00:06:45,330
safely to the destination,

95
00:06:46,070 --> 00:06:47,670
completing their schedule.

96
00:06:47,860 --> 00:06:50,120
I think this is the greatest achievement

97
00:06:50,720 --> 00:06:51,510
as a captain.

98
00:06:59,170 --> 00:06:59,680
Next,

99
00:07:01,530 --> 00:07:02,790
I want to give you

100
00:07:02,820 --> 00:07:04,180
a small gift for you.

101
00:07:13,150 --> 00:07:16,430
This is a luggage tag

102
00:07:16,590 --> 00:07:18,320
made from the external surface

103
00:07:18,460 --> 00:07:19,860
of the 737-300 that year.

104
00:07:20,400 --> 00:07:22,690
Although the plane retired gloriously,

105
00:07:23,710 --> 00:07:25,480
the warning left behind

106
00:07:26,340 --> 00:07:27,270
is always there.

107
00:07:29,420 --> 00:07:31,930
I hope you can always carry

108
00:07:33,100 --> 00:07:35,800
your mission and responsibilities.

109
00:08:06,130 --> 00:08:06,860
All the best.

110
